## UnrecognizedRenderPartialArguments

**Severity:** warning | **Type:** LiquidHtml | **Aliases:** `UnrecognizedRenderPartialParams`

This check ensures that no unknown arguments are used when rendering a partial that has a `{% raw %}{% doc %}{% endraw %}` tag. Passing arguments that the partial does not declare is likely a mistake — either the argument name is misspelled, or the partial's `{% raw %}{% doc %}{% endraw %}` tag needs to be updated.

This check only runs when the target partial has a `{% raw %}{% doc %}{% endraw %}` tag. For partials without a `{% raw %}{% doc %}{% endraw %}` tag, see [MetadataParamsCheck](/developer-guide/platformos-check/checks/metadata-params-check).

## Examples

### &#x2717; Incorrect Code Example (Avoid using this):

```liquid
{% raw %}
{% comment %}app/views/partials/user/card.liquid{% endcomment %}
{% doc %}
  @param {string} name - The user's display name
{% enddoc %}
<div>{{ name }}</div>
{% endraw %}
```

```liquid
{% raw %}
{% comment %}Calling site — 'avatar_url' is not declared in the partial's doc tag{% endcomment %}
{% render 'user/card', name: user.name, avatar_url: user.avatar %}
{% endraw %}
```

### &#x2713; Correct Code Example (Use this instead):

Either remove the unknown argument at the call site:

```liquid
{% raw %}
{% render 'user/card', name: user.name %}
{% endraw %}
```

Or declare the argument in the partial's `{% raw %}{% doc %}{% endraw %}` tag:

```liquid
{% raw %}
{% doc %}
  @param {string} name - The user's display name
  @param {string} [avatar_url] - Optional avatar URL
{% enddoc %}
{% endraw %}
```

## Configuration

The default configuration for this check:

```yaml
UnrecognizedRenderPartialArguments:
  enabled: true
  severity: warning
```

## Disabling This Check

This check can be disabled if you intentionally pass additional context to partials beyond what is declared in the `{% raw %}{% doc %}{% endraw %}` tag.

